          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Duplicate”</p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Curacao</placeName>
                                        <date>October 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1848</date>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">dear Friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">I received your sundry favors <date>2nd<lb/>
                                                  March</date> &amp; <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi>
                                                  May</date>, &amp; <date>21<hi rend="sup">st</hi>
                                                  August</date>, together with all the missing<lb/>
                                        occidents, and a letter from <persName>Mr. J. J.
                                                  Seixas</persName> explaining the<lb/> detentions
                                        of those letters and books having been occasioned<lb/> by
                                        the negligence of our <placeName>New York</placeName>
                                        agents, which I regret<lb/> as it has been the cause of my
                                                  <sic>loosing</sic> many subscribers, I was<lb/>
                                        reduced to 5, but since the books have arrived I have got 2
                                        more<lb/> thus now I have 7 subscribers. In my last I
                                        informed you<lb/> of my having disposed of one Sett of
                                        Prayer Books, since<lb/> which tho we have passed all the
                                        holidays which is the time to sell<lb/> I have not been able
                                        to dispose of a single Sett, they all com=<lb/>plain the
                                        books are too large and heavy. So much so that I<lb/> have
                                        orders for three Setts if printed on thin paper like your
                                        Daily<lb/> Services, and as they fear you will not have them
                                        bound as<lb/> they wish, <hi rend="underline">that is to say
                                                  one of the persons</hi>, he requests you will<lb/>
                                        send him out <hi rend="underline">an unbound Sett</hi> if on
                                        thin paper, his object is to<lb/> cut off the margins as
                                        much as possible, and then have<lb/> them bound in smaller
                                        vols. according to his own taste<lb/> they being for a very
                                        young lady who could not well<lb/> hold <sic>ones</sic> of
                                        these books in her hands the time she should<lb/> in
                                        consequence of the weight, the other two setts you will<lb/>
                                        please send according to the order enclosed, all three<lb/>
                                        Setts are bespoken consequently they must be</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>according to the order, and those you cant fulfill (if<lb/> any)
                                        according to the order do not send at all as I<lb/> am
                                        exposed to receive them on my hands, you would<lb/> do well
                                        also to put up a few setts more for me to sell<lb/> with at
                                        least the kipur books divided in two or three, and<lb/>
                                        always on thin paper, as those heavy books will not
                                        sell.<lb/> the <placeName>west India</placeName> ladies will
                                        not use them, the English<lb/> editions being so much
                                        smaller or lighter. I am very<lb/> much obliged to you for
                                        the notice you took of my dear<lb/> wife's death. The
                                        sentiments expressed being your own<lb/> I am doubly
                                        thankful. I would surmise in the price<lb/> of the books you
                                        charge them 5 per cent over your price as<lb/> here 5 franc
                                        pieces pay for Dollars, and if you require re=<lb/>mittance
                                        in that specie you will have to <sic>loose</sic> the
                                        dif=<lb/>-ference, however you do not mention any thing of
                                        that<lb/> in yr letter as I may perhaps have to shew it to
                                        them.</p>
                              <p>In your kind favor of <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> May.</date> I
                                        perceive w/ much<lb/> pleasure your promise to send my
                                        sister <persName>Mrs.<lb/> Lindo</persName> a number of the
                                        Occident I have written her<lb/> to that effect, and have
                                        requested her to apply to your<lb/> agents in
                                                  <placeName>London</placeName>, if she does not
                                        hear from them,<lb/> with the sett of prayer Books here in
                                        ordered to be<lb/> sent unbound please send (on same sort
                                        paper &amp; same <add>?</add>)<lb/> a Sett of Pentateuch
                                        unbound, as the person wishes to<lb/> have them, forming one
                                        complete Sett all bound alike<lb/> and all printed alike. I
                                        will copy below this the<lb/> order he has given me in his
                                        own words to avoid mis=<lb/>takes. Hoping you have passed
                                        pleasantly the holidays &amp; that you may<lb/> see many
                                        happy returns of them. I am yr Sincere friend.</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>PS. In your favor of <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi>: March</date>,
                                        you say the Books I<lb/> ordered for <placeName>Pto
                                                  Cabello</placeName> will go by the next
                                        packet,<lb/> now I do not recollect having ordered any
                                        Books<lb/> for <placeName>Pto Cabo.</placeName>, or any
                                        where else, if you have sent<lb/> any please let me
                                        know.—</p>
                              <p><hi rend="underline">Copy</hi>: One Sett Prayer Books</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">One Ditto Pentateuch all printed on thin<lb/>
                                        paper, to be unbound, the person wants to get<lb/> them
                                        bound here, that he may divide them to his liking<lb/> and
                                        his motive for wishing thin paper's because<lb/> he wanted
                                        them for his young daughter, consequently<lb/> he wants them
                                        light, if they cant be sent according<lb/> to his
                                                  <sic>desine</sic> do not send them.</p>
                              <p><date>Decr. 8.</date> Dr Sir.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">The foregoing is duplicate of my last
                                        respects<lb/> since which I have recd. yr. favors <date>3
                                                  Oct.</date> &amp; <date>31<hi rend="sup"
                                                  >st</hi></date> and the<lb/> Books correct as per
                                        your notes.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr. Dacosta</persName> left this morning
                                        for <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> to<lb/> fetch out his
                                        sister who is coming out from
                                        <placeName>England</placeName><lb/> to join him here,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I am afraid you will never see the money if<lb/>
                                        the books <persName>Mr. Lobo</persName> of <placeName>Puerto
                                                  Cavello</placeName> had from you<lb/> ask is not
                                        the best paymaster, I hope tho' it<lb/> will prove
                                        otherwise.—wishing you well, and<lb/> with respect I am Dr
                                        Sir yrs. Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">
                                        <persName>O U Dacosta</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">pp. <persName role="author"><hi rend="underline"
                                                  >John E. Price</hi></persName></p>
                              <p>Encld. A letter recd for you</p>
                              <p>frm. <placeName>Suriname</placeName>.</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <del>care of the <add>?</add>
                                                  <persName>Joseph E</persName><add>?</add><lb/>
                                                  <placeName>New York</placeName></del>
                              </p>
                    </body>
